author: Malcolm Ross, fieldnotes (ca 1981), supplemented from Hiroko Sato,fieldnotes (2015) and an anonymous SIL short wordlist
problems: There are dialect differences within Avau (Hiroko Sato, pers. comm.), but it is not clear whether the few differences between sources here reflect a difference in dialect or the passing of time. Items from Sato's list are annotated 'hs'. Items that occurred in  Ross's (or SIL's) list are unmarked.
classification: Austronesian, Malayo-Polynesian, Central-Eastern Malayo-Polynesian, Eastern Malayo-Polynesian, Oceanic, Western Oceanic, North New Guinea, Ngero-Vitiaz, Vitiaz, Southwest New Britain, Arawe-Pasismanua, Arawe, East Arawe
